Ensuring Integrity: Comparing Remote Proctoring Methods and Their Effectiveness
Home » Ensuring Integrity: Comparing Remote Proctoring Methods and Their Effectiveness

Published on: December 10, 2024 by thinkexam.com
Ensuring Integrity Comparing Remote Proctoring Methods and Their Effectiveness
In recent years, we have seen a booming rise in the use of online schooling. As a result, the need for better assessment techniques has increased. As such, in case of cheating problems, educational institutions and organisations tend to have more reliance on proctoring software and solutions. This article presents different types of remote proctoring services available, examines how useful they are, and how they contribute to the prevention of cheating in online examinations.

What is Remote Proctoring?
Remote proctoring is a method where students are monitored remotely during exams ensuring the integrity of papers and preventing cheating. Such services make it possible for the organisation to run a secure assessment test from anywhere. 

With the introduction of remote proctoring tools, no matter the distance from the institution, exam-takers, and access to cheating during the online assessment has been controlled. These proctoring tools make use of complex technologies, including that of an AI proctor, to create a non-bias environment for the conduct of the exams.

Different Types of Remote Proctoring:- 
1. Live Online Proctoring:
This method involves the use of web cameras and microphones through which candidates being supervised are monitored in real time by a proctor. This tool of remote proctoring enables response to the way in which a test-taker behaves and any other irregularities that may arise during the exam. The level of effectiveness of live proctoring is very high because there is a human factor. That’s why proctors can interact with students directly, which is very helpful.

– Advantages:

Monitoring in real-time provides extra security.
Proctors are able to solve problems right away.
– Disadvantages:

Both the proctor and test taker must have a reliable internet connection.
Additional costs are incurred mainly due to extra human proctors.
2. Automated Proctoring Screenshots:
Automated Proctoring, A.D.E.D. solutions incorporate strategic innovative systems to survey students while carrying out exams. Such systems scrutinise the visual channels and track abnormal attributes like focusing movement as well as the placement of kinetic elements. Seamless remote proctoring minimises operational challenges for organisations seeking to enroll a significant number of students.

– Advantages: 

More economical than conducting examination with an invigilator in person.
Allows for easy administration and management even on a multitude of expansion.
– Disadvantages: 

There are chances of false alarm and it’s attendant hysterics.
Does not provide any human interaction, as is always the case with live proctoring.
3. Record-and-Review Proctoring:
Record-and-review proctoring involves capturing the exam oriented session in a video that can subsequently be assessed by a supervising individual. Institutions encourage compliance with this method whilst lessening the immediacy of a proctor’s presence. This remote proctoring method is perfect for firms that desire safety and ease in equal measure.

– Advantages:

It allows for flexibility of the exam takers.
Minimises the requirement for real time observation.
– Disadvantages:

Unfair practices may be witnessed if the reinforcement of recording does not come as a surprise to the students.
The review process takes a longer duration than expected for the proctors tending to it.
Introducing Think Proctor: Leading Remote Proctoring Software:-
Despite its many shortcomings, Think Proctor powered by Think Exam remains one of the many developments in remote proctoring that is developed to fulfil the emerging demand of the education sectors and also the governments and corporations. 
Think Proctor provides a complete range of services to meet all the proctoring requirements for the conducting of online examinations without compromising on the level of comfort experienced by both the exam conducting authorities and the candidates.
Key Features of Remote Proctoring:
AI Based Image Proctoring: With Think Proctor innovative remote proctoring services, world’s powerful images blended with high-end technology are used for candidate identity check, thus, ensuring that a candidate’s examination is not held by any other person at any point of time. 
AI Based ID Verification: This feature is also important because it prevents other people from taking exams on behalf of candidates by checking candidate’s ID before starting the exam and during the exam as well. The process may involve taking a video recording for the entire examination procedure allowing for its assessment later on making it ideal in circumstances where active overseeing is impossible. 
Live Monitoring: In case of high-stakes exams, Think Proctor offers a live stream of proctors who will watch all candidates and resolve any given problem immediately when noticed.
With Think Proctor’s remote proctoring method, organisations are able to change from doing conventional room-killed exams to onscreen assessment without compromising the limits. The platform is designed in a way that smart and advanced technologies are fitted in the most simple manner to the users of the system who are the students sitting for examinations while strict supervision is ensured.

Opt for the Best Proctoring Methodology:-
Determining the most suitable remote proctoring method takes into consideration many aspects including the kind of examination, security level, economic factors among other things. Schools must consider the advantages and disadvantages of each method in order to select the best online proctored exam team that serves their purpose.

And with Think Proctor you will find the best online proctoring services and team that will ensure the prevention of cheating as well as the integrity of examinations.

Important Considerations:-
Exam Format: The nature of the assessment being offered may determine the kind of remote proctoring solution that is adopted. For instance, in the case of high stakes tests, it may be more appropriate to employ live or automated proctoring instead.
Facility Budget: The pricing for provision of remote proctoring solutions should correspond with the institution’s ability to avoid compromising the quality of examination. 
User Experience: It is important to select proctoring systems that will be easy for the students to use in order to reduce the stress levels and likelihood of any technical glitches during examinations.
Conclusion:-
As education progresses with current changes that allow for online assessment, keeping the honesty of students taking such examinations should be a priority. Such comparisons help institutions choose the appropriative remote proctoring method which ensures academic integrity as well as safe testing.

