FAQs:-
1. What are the rules for remote proctoring?
One of the most important rules for proctoring is to keep your camera and microphone on throughout the exam. The sessions are recorded and reviewed by assigned proctors in case of any questionable behaviour. Verification of identity using a photo ID that has your name and photo on the same side is a must.
2. How is online proctoring done?
Same as offline proctoring, online remote proctoring starts with authentication. With the help of software, the candidate’s authenticity is checked. The system makes sure that the examinee is sharing their screen with audio and video recording before the test.
3. Is talking to ourselves allowed during a proctored exam?
It is recommended to not talk or mumble to yourself or even look around the room, because the proctor doesn’t know whether you are talking to yourself or someone else. 
4. Who is the best online remote proctoring service provider?
With many years of experience in this field, the one name that stands out the most among the race of numerous software, Think Proctor is renowned as the best online remote proctoring software where innovation takes place.
